<topic xml:id="ha-resources-configuring-clones"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Configuring resource clones</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tahlia.richardson@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <xi:include href="../snippets/ha-resources-clones.xml"/>
    </abstract>
  </info>

  <para>
    You can configure resource clones with the &crmshell; (&crmsh;) or with the &hawk; Web interface.
  </para>

  <itemizedlist>
    <title>Requirements</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The primitive or group already exists.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis>For promotable clones</emphasis>: the primitive has two monitor operations:
        one for when the resource is in the unpromoted role, and one with a different interval
        for when the resource is in the promoted role.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis>For promotable clones</emphasis>: the resource agent supports the promote
        and demote operations.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>

  <variablelist role="tabs">
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&crmshell;</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can perform this procedure on any node in the cluster.
        </para>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              Log in either as the &rootuser; user or as a user with <command>sudo</command> privileges.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Configure a clone. The basic command requires a name and one primitive or group:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure clone <replaceable>CLONE_NAME RESOURCE</replaceable></command></screen>
            <variablelist>
              <title>Additional options</title>
              <varlistentry>
                <term>Meta attributes</term>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    Clones can have additional clone-specific meta attributes, such as
                    <literal>clone-max</literal> or <literal>globally-unique</literal>.
                    For more information about the meta attributes for clones, see
                    <link xlink:href="https://clusterlabs.org/projects/pacemaker/doc/3.0/Pacemaker_Explained/html/collective.html#clone-options"/>
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </varlistentry>
              <varlistentry>
                <term>Promotable clones</term>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    To configure a promotable clone, add the meta attribute
                    <literal>promotable=true</literal>:
                  </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm configure clone clone1 res1 meta promotable=true</command></screen>
                  <para>
                    Promotable clones can also have additional meta attributes:
                    <literal>promoted-max</literal> and <literal>promoted-node-max</literal>.
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Check the cluster status to make sure the clone set is running on all nodes:
            </para>
<screen>&prompt.user;<command>sudo crm status</command></screen>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&hawk;</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can use &hawk; on any machine with a Web browser and network access to the nodes.
        </para>
        <procedure>
          <step>
            <para>
              In a Web browser, go to
              <literal>https://<replaceable>HAWKSERVER</replaceable>:7630/</literal>
              and log in.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              From the left navigation bar, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Configuration</guimenu>
              <guimenu>Add Resource</guimenu></menuchoice>.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>Clone</guimenu> for a standard clone<!--, or
              <guimenu>Multi-state</guimenu> for a promotable clone-->.
            </para>
            <important role="compact">
              <para>
                Currently, &hawk; can only create standard clones, not promotable clones.
              </para>
              <!-- Fix when https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1267908 is done -->
            </important>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Enter a unique <guimenu>Clone ID</guimenu><!-- or <guimenu>Multi-state ID</guimenu>-->.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              From the <guimenu>Child Resource</guimenu> drop-down list, select the primitive or
              group to clone.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step performance="optional">
            <para>
              Add <guimenu>Meta Attributes</guimenu> by selecting them from the drop-down list.
            </para>
            <para>
              Clones can have additional meta attributes that define how the clone behaves.
              <!--Promotable clones can also have further meta attributes that define how many
              of the clones can be promoted.-->
            </para>
            <para>
              You can hover the cursor over each meta attribute to see a description.
            </para>
          </step>
          <step>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu> to finish the configuration.
            </para>
            <para>
              A message at the top of the screen shows if the action was successful.
            </para>
          </step>
        </procedure>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <itemizedlist>
    <title>For more information</title>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <command>crm configure help clone</command>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <link xlink:href="https://clusterlabs.org/projects/pacemaker/doc/3.0/Pacemaker_Explained/html/collective.html#clones-resources-that-can-have-multiple-active-instances"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
